Alan Beck wrote:
> Hi,
> I have been losing about 1 Litre per 50 KM's of oil.
> When hot, the engine drips a lot.

What might look like a minor leak from a pushrod can actually be a major 
leak.  Plus, the cooling air can blow the oil everywhere, which can be 
deceiving.

I use the aviation form-a-gasket and don't have any pushrod tube leaks.

